---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Teaching"
  description="Teaching in generative and agentic AI with a practical, evaluation-oriented focus."
>
  <Section title="Teaching">
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        My teaching in Generative and Agentic AI combines academic rigor with practical
        implementation.
      </p>
      <p>
        The curriculum is organized around foundations, reproducible system design, and applied use
        cases in healthcare and other domains.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Core Topics">
    <div class="list">
      <article class="item">
        <h3>Generative and Agentic AI: Foundations, Frameworks, and Applications</h3>
        <p class="meta">Academic framing with implementation-first practice</p>
        <ul>
          <li>LLM fundamentals</li>
          <li>Prompt design and prompt engineering patterns</li>
          <li>Retrieval-augmented generation (RAG)</li>
          <li>Agentic workflows and tool-using systems</li>
          <li>Evaluation methodologies for reliability and performance</li>
          <li>Practical local and open model stacks</li>
          <li>Healthcare and applied AI use cases</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Teaching Approach">
    <div class="list">
      <article class="item">
        <h3>Academic but Practical</h3>
        <p>
          Teaching emphasizes hands-on implementation, careful reading of key papers, and
          end-to-end system building.
        </p>
        <p>
          A core goal is understanding AI limitations: where methods generalize, where they fail,
          and how evaluation and validation should guide deployment decisions.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
